%% Card Resolution Flow Diagram 
%% Last Updated: 3/18/2026
%% Version: 1.0

%% Purpose
%% To explain the flow of a card being drawn from the chance or community deck within the game along with the decisions that need to occur. 

%% Scope
%% The card chance and community chest resolution logic

flowchart TD
    A[Player lands on Chance or Community Chest space] --> B[Trigger card draw]
    B --> C{Deck has cards?}

    C -->|Yes| D[Draw top card]
    C -->|No| E[Reshuffle discard pile]
    E --> D

    D --> F[Reveal card]
    F --> G{Card effect type?}

    %%Movement cards
    G --> M1[Move to a specific space]
    M1 --> M2[Update player position]
    M2 --> M3[Apply rules of new space]

    %%Money cards
    G --> P1[Money gain or loss]
    P1 --> P2{Receive or pay?}
    P2 -->|Receive| P3[Add to player cash]
    P2 -->|Pay| P4[Player pays money]
    P4 --> P5{Can player pay?}
    P5 -->|Yes| P6[Deduct cash]
    P5 -->|No| P7[Handle mortgage or bankruptcy]

    %%Go to Jail
    G --> J1[Go to Jail]
    J1 --> J2[Move player to Jail]
    J2 --> J3[Mark player as in Jail]

    %% et Out of Jail Free
    G --> O1[Get Out of Jail Free card]
    O1 --> O2[Place card in player inventory]

    %%Repairs
    G --> R1[House or hotel repair cost]
    R1 --> R2[Calculate total amount]
    R2 --> R3{Can player pay?}
    R3 -->|Yes| R4[Deduct cash]
    R3 -->|No| P7

    %%Other effect
    G --> X1[Other special effect]
    X1 --> X2[Apply effect]

    %%Discard card
    M3 --> Z[Discard card]
    P3 --> Z
    P6 --> Z
    P7 --> Z
    J3 --> Z
    O2 --> Z
    R4 --> Z
    X2 --> Z

    Z --> END[End card resolution]
